  "patient_summary": "Olivia is a 73-year-old female with a history of hyperlipidemia associated with type 2 diabetes mellitus, MRSA, and recovered COVID-19. Social history indicates she is a former smoker who quit in 1991 and does not currently consume alcohol. Functional status assessments show she has difficulty walking or climbing stairs, but her vision is adequate for daily activities, and she reports no difficulty with hearing, dressing, bathing, errands, concentrating, remembering, or making decisions. Recent lab results indicate elevated Ferritin and low Iron and Iron Saturation, consistent with iron deficiency. She has upcoming office visits with various specialists through late 2025, including cardiology, pulmonology, and gastroenterology, and has a scheduled colonoscopy with biopsy in February 2025. Her care team includes specialists in family medicine, endocrinology, cardiology, general surgery, oncology, optometry, and nephrology. She actively manages blood pressure and diabetes with specific blood sugar goals, but has reported being off-track with an eye doctor appointment and expressed a wish to get off insulin."
